@Masz52
Sorry, but the classic controller just doesn't cut it. You have to plug it into a Wii remote and use batteries. That's 4 Wii remotes, 4 classic controllers, and 8 batteries, just to play a game with normal controllers with your friends. That's ridiculous.
The Wii had the advantage of working with the Gamecube controller, but it doesn't seem like the Wii U is going to do that. Nintendo REALLY needs to make new standard controllers that work ON THEIR OWN with the Wii U.
